<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Guess the Bureaucracy:  Week 2</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">
<CENTER><H2>Guess the Bureaucracy</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
This week's Town Hall Spotlight provides you with the chance to learn a little bit about some more of the organizations that run on your hard earned money--government bureaucracies.
 More bureaucracies were featured in last week's Spotlight, and they are now labeled and linked to relevant articles.  <a href="/townhall/infotain/12-11-95/answers.html">Check it out!</a>

<br>

<A HREF="8.jpg"><IMG SRC="8.gif" ALT="PHOTO" align="left"></A><h3><a href="http://www.dot.gov">US Department of Transportation</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>This department was created in 1966 to oversee the growth in urban mass transit programs, air traffic, and construction of the Interstate Highway System.
<li>Because each member of Congress tries to assure that his or her state or district recieve as much pork as possible, this department regularly funds expensive, low-priority projects over more sensible, appropriate ones.
<li>Congress earmaked 129 surface projects, at an annual cost of $250 million in FY 1995. During the same year, $1.5 billion was appropriated for airport grants-in-aid, including nearly $5 million for the Jimmy Stewart Airport in Indiana County, Pennsylvania.
<li>19% (18,000 workers) of its civilian staff was furloughed in the first government shutdown.
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/budgettax/bg1048.html ">How to Close Down the Department of Transportation -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/regulation/bg958.html ">The Airline Commission's Boost for Deregulation -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/commentary/op-ef2.html ">Drivers Could Get Speedy Win...  -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/enviro/bg825.html ">Auto Cafe Standards: Unsafe and Unwise at Any Level  -- Heritage </A><BR></ul>



<A HREF="9.jpg"><IMG SRC="9.gif" ALT="PHOTO" align="left"></A><h3><a href="http://www.dtic.dla.mil/defenselink">US Department of Defense</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Made infamous in the 1980s for purchasing $12 "portable language inscribers" (a.k.a. "pencils"), $45 hammers, and $130 toilet seats, this bureaucracy has shaped up considerably in recent years.
<li>The Clinton Administration underfunded even its own Bottom-Up Review of this Department by $100 million in 1995, and neglected to budget for unexpected emergency actions, like the one to Haiti.
<li>258,000 civilian employees (31% of its overall staff), labelled non-essential, didn't show have to commute to this 5-sided building during the first shutdown.
<LI><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/pr1thomp.html ">The Readiness Trap -- Heritage </A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="/townhall/FRC/infocus/if95a5hm.html ">End Civilian Judges' Abuse of the Military -- Heritage </A><BR>
<LI><<A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bg1042.html ">More Military Bases Need to Be Closed -- Heritage </A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bg964.html "> Suporting the Force:  The Industrial Base and Defense Conversion -- Heritage </A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/em424.html ">The Defense Budget:  Why Nunn-Lugar Money Should Go to the B-2 -- Heritage </A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bgu244.html ">Defense Freeze Would Harm U.S. Security -- Heritage </A><BR>
<LI><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bgu217.html ">Clinton's Defense Budget Falls Far Short  -- Heritage </A><BR>
</ul>

<hr width="50%">

<P><P>
<A HREF="10.jpg"><IMG SRC="10.gif" ALT="PHOTO" align="left"></A><h3><a href="http://www.os.dhhs.gov">US Department of Health and Human Services</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Sent home 34,600 workers (58% of civilian staff) during the first shutdown.
<li>Is part of the largest spending bill Congress produces annually.
<li><A HREF="/govt-waste/LookingGlass/embezz.html ">Medicare Fraud: Tales From the Gypped -- CAGW</A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/govt-waste/RealityChecks/realit2.html "> Reality Checks -- CAGW</A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/townhall/columnists/dupl1002.html ">Duplantier:  The Problems With Health Maintenance Organizations -- 10/2/95 </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/townhall/FRC/whois/hamdoc.html ">Teens, big business and the politics of sex -- FRC</A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/healthwel/em428.html ">Two Cheers For the House Medicare Plan -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/govt-waste/CapitolHill/CongressTestimony/testmed.html "> Congressional Testimony -- CAGW</A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/healthwel/lect538.html ">The Medicare Debate: Politics, Process, and Proposals for Reform -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/townhall/FRC/insight/is95c2dr.html ">Legalization of Drugs:  The Myths and the Facts -- FRC </A><BR>

</ul>


<hr width="50%">
<P><P>
<A HREF="11.jpg"><IMG SRC="11.gif" ALT="PHOTO" align="left"></A><h3><a href="http://www.house.gov">US House of Reps.</a> | <a href="http://www.senate.gov">US Senate</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Its operating costs have ballooned by over 800 percent in the last thirty years, but did cut its 1996 budget to $2.2 billion, down from $2.4 billion in 1995.
<li>It recently came under the same environmental and workplace regulations that had long been imposed on all other organizations nationwide.
<li>Its 1995 appropriations bill eliminated 2,350 positions, 8.6% of its workforce.
<li>Since November 1994, it has been "Under New Management."
</ul>

<hr width="50%">
<P><P>
<A HREF="12.jpg"><IMG SRC="12.gif" ALT="PHOTO" align="left"></A><h3><a href="http://www.dosfan.lib.uic.edu/dosfan.html">US Department of State</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>90% of its civilian staff was labelled non-essential during the shutdown in early November.
<li>This department is part of our maze of overlapping departments, bureaus, and agencies designed to win the Cold War.
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/cb3.html ">Focus on Free Markets:  How to Cut Foreign Aid -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/em402.html ">Abolish the Wasteful Agenct for International Development  -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/bg1052.html ">The Voice of America: Dont Silence America's Voice in the Global Marketplace of Ideas -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/natsec/bgu240.html ">After World Trade Center Bombing, U.S. Needs Stronger Anti-Terrorism Policy -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/library/categories/forpol/em416.html ">Clinton Blows Smoke Over Foreign Aid Cuts -- Heritage </A><BR>
<li><A HREF="/heritage/p_review/fall95/thsymp.html "> Beyond the Water's Edge -- Fall 95 Policy Review </A><BR>



</ul>

<hr width="50%">
<P><P>
<A HREF="13.jpg"><IMG SRC="13.gif" ALT="PHOTO" align="left"></A><h3><a href="http://www.whitehouse.gov">The White House</a></h3>
<ul>
<li>Once contained the entire Presidential staff , but that staff now occupies two entire builings, each larger than this original structure.
<li>89% (357 employees) of its core staff and 82% (1,000) members of its agencies were deemed "non-essential" by the OMB.
<li>Will hopefully be frequented by an army of moving trucks come December, 1996.
</ul>

<br>
<P>
