<img src="lists.gif">
<h2>Directory of Conservative Listservs</h2>
</center><font size="-1"><i>
This is a list of some of the conservative listservs and mailing lists that are available on the internet.  By listing a list Town Hall does not imply it's endorsement and cannot be held responsible for any content contained within a list.  If you know of any other lists that Town Hall users might benefit from please email <a href="mailto:jgarth@townhall.com">jgarth@townhall.com</a>.
</font>
</i>
<p>
<center>
<table><tr><td>
<a href="/townhall/listserv/">Conservative Quote of the Day</a>
<br>
<a href="/townhall/listserv/">The Town Hall Pamplet</a>
<br>
<A HREF="mailto:majordomo@world.std.com">C-NEWS</A>, 
<em>conservative
 politics, news and information mailing list</em>
<br>
<a href="mailto:cei@access.digex.net">CEI</a>, <em>Competitive 
Enterprise Institute</em>
<br>
<a href="mailto:conservative-request@dragon.com">The Conservative
Coffee House</a>
<br>
<a href="mailto:listserv@psuvm.psu.edu">ELITE</a>, <em>conservative
discussion and analysis mailing list</em>
<br>
<a href="mailto:listserv@umrvmb.umr.edu">PRIMARY</a>, <em>Republican 
primary mailing list</em>
<br>
<a href="mailto:majordomo@wc62.residence.gatech.edu">REPUBLIC</a>, 
<em>Georgia Tech College Republicans</em>
<br>
<a href="mailto:listserv@vm.marist.edu">REPUBLICANS96</a>,
<em>discussion of Republicans running for office in '96</em>
<br>
<a href="http://www.rnc.org/post/majordomo/">RNC "Press" & "Monday Briefing" lists</a>
</td></tr></table>
