<html>
<head>
<title>Pete Du Pont</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/townhall/background.jpg">
<center><h2>Pete Du Pont</h2></center>
<p>
<hr>
<p>
Pete du Pont has served as a state legislator, U.S. Congressman, Governor, and in l988 was a 
Republican candidate for President of the United States.  He writes a weekly column and is a featured 
columnist for CEO Magazine.  He hosts a weekly television program entitled FocusPoint for National 
Empowerment Television (NET) and various broadcast stations.
<p>
	Pete du Pont chairs the Strategic Advisory Committee, which advises Speaker Newt Gingrich on 
key strategic issues, and was appointed to the National Commission on Economic Growth and Tax Reform, 
known as the Kemp Commission.  du Pont is currently Policy Chairman of the National Center for 
Policy Analysis and Chairman of the National Review Institute, public policy analysis organizations 
promoting free enterprise and conservative governmental policies.   He has served as Chairman of the 
Hudson Institute and was the founder of GOPAC, the Republican political action committee.
<p>
	Pete du Pont began his political career in l968 with his election to the Delaware General 
Assembly.  In l970, he was elected to the U.S. House of Representatives, where he served for six years.
<p>
	In l976, Pete du Pont won the race for Delaware Governor against the Democratic incumbent 
and was re-elected in l980 to a second term, winning a record 7l% of the vote.  During his tenure as 
Delaware's Governor, du Pont restored financial integrity to the state government.  Known for his fiscal 
conservatism, he signed into law two income tax reduction measures and a constitutional amendment that 
restrained future tax increases and limited government spending.  He balanced his state budget eight out of 
eight years.
<p>
	Throughout his public policy career, Pete du Pont has addressed a wide range of critical issues 
and has developed a reputation for taking on the toughest challenges and successfully meeting them.  In his 
campaign for the Presidency, his focus upon the central issues facing our country -- drugs, education, 
retirement income, poverty, defense and our relationship with the Soviet Union -- earned him a reputation 
as a man with a long-range vision and the courage to speak the truth about tomorrow.
<p>
	Columnist George Will said about du Pont's l988 campaign:<p>  "du Pont has the highest 
substance-to-blather ratio among candidates, even on subjects as sensitive as agriculture policy and Social 
Security."
<p>
	Upon his withdrawal from the 1988 race, Scripps Howard News Service noted, "More than any 
rival in either party, du Pont had the courage to tell specific interest groups what they least wanted to hear.
<p>
	Rush Limbaugh recently stated Pete du Pont...[is one of the] people who have paved the way 
for me to succeed.<p>
[<a href="/townhall/columnists/welcome.html.cgi">Columnists</a>]
</html>









	


